    },
    {
      "id": "bb61ed9d-d82d-4323-99f1-ad6b5f6612a9",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 140,
        "y": 150
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "Q1 - PNP Transistor/Amplifier",
        "text": "The input stage is a Common Emitter (Collector Follower) PNP amplifier, it provides a high voltage gain with low input impedance and high output impedance. It is not the ideal input stage for signal integrity but the best for simplicity and fast high gain.",
        "color": "blue",
        "size": "sm",
        "width": "normal"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 160,
        "height": 94
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
    {
      "id": "81dd95ac-b144-4e1f-8a27-eefee80d7aaf",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 190,
        "y": 320
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "C1",
        "text": "The 2.2uF input capacitor C1 blocks any DC level, removing hum and protecting the pedal/guitar against dangerous DC levels.",
        "color": "blue",
        "size": "xs",
        "width": "slim"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 80,
        "height": 80
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c82433fa-0b75-489c-ad15-a6dade82830f",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 360,
        "y": 130
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "R1",
        "text": "The 33KΩ R1 resistor sets the main input stage parameters like the voltage gain, bias points, and maximum collector current.",
        "color": "blue",
        "size": "xs",
        "width": "slim"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 80,
        "height": 80
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c6030637-018a-4cab-96a1-0967c653fa79",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 360,
        "y": 520
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "R4 - Feedback Strength",
        "text": "R4 sets the amount of available feedback path, and the FUZZ pot controls how much of that feedback actually stays in circuit",
        "color": "green",
        "size": "sm",
        "width": "normal"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 160,
        "height": 80
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
    {
      "id": "50dc4e94-bd2f-4d3c-ba82-7e7681315bed",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": 130
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "VOLUME",
        "text": "The final part of the circuit defines how loud the circuit is. Depending on the position of the pot, the signal is split between going to ground and going to the output jack.",
        "color": "pink",
        "size": "sm",
        "width": "normal"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 160,
        "height": 80
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c1a32d3c-bd02-464e-ad62-5549ed78cb96",
      "type": "stickynote",
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": 30
      },
      "data": {
        "label": "C3",
        "text": "C3 is an output coupling cap. It blocks DC from the transistor and, with the volume control, forms a high-pass filter that sets how much low end gets out",
        "color": "pink",
        "size": "sm",
        "width": "normal"
      },
      "measured": {
        "width": 160,
        "height": 80
      },
      "selected": false,
      "dragging": false
    },
